Deconvolution of WGS lung samples

Giulio Caravagna

12/03/2020

require(dplyr)
require(mobster)
require(BMix)

We describe the analysis of samples LUFF76 and LU4; the calls that we used are freely available at the COALA, Comprehensive Omics Archive of Lung Adenocarcinoma, database.

We have included the results from our analysis of these samples as data released with MOBSTER.

This page describes the analysis of one of the two samples; the analysis of any other lung sample presented in the text is carried out exactly in the same way. The analysis of the other breast cancer and AML cases is also done in the same way, but those calls you are required to collect the data from the original papers due to copyright issues.

# Fit object
LU4_fit = mobster::LU4_lung_sample

# print and plot
print(LU4_fit$best)

Downstram read counts based analysis with BMix.


# Non-tail mutations
non_tail_mutations = mobster::Clusters(fit$best) %>% filter(cluster != "Tail")

print(non_tail_mutations)
#> # A tibble: 972 x 14
#>      Key Callers t_alt_count t_ref_count Variant_Classif…    DP   VAF chr  
#>    <int> <chr>         <int>       <int> <chr>            <int> <dbl> <chr>
#>  1   370 mutect…          30          95 intergenic         125 0.24  chr2 
#>  2   372 mutect…          40         108 intronic           148 0.270 chr2 
#>  3   373 mutect…          20         101 intronic           121 0.165 chr2

#>  6   376 mutect…          43          93 intronic           136 0.316 chr2 
#>  7   377 mutect…          22          95 intergenic         117 0.188 chr2 
#>  8   379 mutect…          35          93 intergenic         128 0.273 chr2 
#>  9   380 mutect…          35          95 intergenic         130 0.269 chr2 
#> 10   381 mutect…          34         121 intergenic         155 0.219 chr2 
#> # … with 962 more rows, and 6 more variables: from <chr>, ref <chr>, alt <chr>,
#> #   cluster <chr>, Tail <dbl>, C1 <dbl>

# DP is t_alt_count + t_ref_count; NV is t_alt_count
DP = non_tail_mutations %>% select(DP)
NV = non_tail_mutations %>% select(t_alt_count)

colnames(DP) = colnames(NV) = "SAMPLE"

# fit by BMix
rfit = bmixfit(cbind(NV, DP))
#>  [ BMix fit ]
#> ℹ Binomials k_B = 1 and 2, Beta-Binomials k_BB = 0.
#> ✓ Fits to run, n = 4.
#> ℹ Bmix best fit completed in 0.01 mins
#> ── [ BMix ] My BMix model n = 972 with k = 1 component(s) (1 + 0) ──────────────
#> ● Clusters: π = 100% [Bin 1], with π > 0.
#> ● Binomial Bin 1 with mean = 0.260994935665996.
#> ℹ Score(s): ICL = 6739.89.

# Print and plot the fit
print(rfit)
#> ── [ BMix ] My BMix model n = 972 with k = 1 component(s) (1 + 0) ──────────────
#> ● Clusters: π = 100% [Bin 1], with π > 0.
#> ● Binomial Bin 1 with mean = 0.260994935665996.
#> ℹ Score(s): ICL = 6739.89.
BMix::plot_clusters(rfit, data = cbind(NV, DP))
